article.headline: Jacksonville 73, Gardner-Webb 64
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Jesse Kimbrough scored 14 points as Jacksonville defeated Gardner-Webb 73-64 Tuesday. The game got off to a close start and there were seven lead changes in the first half, which ended tied at 35. In the second half, a lay up from Auryn MacMillan put Gardner-Webb (2-10, 0-1 Atlantic Sun Conference) ahead 62-61 with 4:03 left. Kimbrough's two free throws sparked a 9-0 Jacksonville run that put the game away. The Bulldogs shot 12-of-27 from 3-point range, but were outrebounded 42-30 and outscored in the paint 32-20. The Dolphins (5-8, 1-2) had 27 points off turnovers while committing a season-low 12. It was Jacksonville's first Atlantic Sun Conference win since December 2005. Gardner-Webb's Chris Gash was 5-of-10 on 3-pointers and finished with a game-high 17 points, 12 of which came in the first half. Jake Sims added 14 points and forward Marcus Allen had 11 points and a game-high eight rebounds for Jacksonville.
